# 1. Ignore absolutely everything in the repository by default
*

# 2. Un-ignore directories (Git needs this to traverse the file tree)
!*/

# 3. Whitelist your source code and project files
!*.c
!README.md
!.gitignore

# 4. Whitelist your seed input directory and the files inside it
!in/
!in/*

# 5. Explicitly re-ignore fuzzer output directories, just to be safe
# (Prevents Git from tracking things like out/default/crashes/README.txt)
out/
out_*/